news.title: Mumbai Police arrest builder in New India Citizen Cooperative Bank case
news.para: According to officials, Mehta and an unidentified accomplice allegedly conspired to siphon off the massive sum between May 2019 and January 2025.

news.title: Over 8,000 complaints pending with Maharashtra RERA
news.para: With around 8,000 complaints pending, besides delay in or non-execution of some of the regulator's orders, including recovery warrants by revenue authorities, experts say it "lacks teeth and needs to do more".

news.title: Begin construction of Indiramma houses: Telangana deputy CM tells officials
news.para: At a pre-budget review with the officials of the two departments, Bhatti said CM A Revanth Reddy stated that the construction of Indiramma houses should start immediately in Mahabubnagar and Rangareddy districts too, where the MLC poll code is not in force.

news.title: Enzyme Office Spaces lease out 14,000 sq ft space to SUGAR Cosmetics
news.para: Enzyme Office Spaces founder and CEO Ashish Agarwal said the company has given on lease 14,000 square feet workspace to SUGAR Cosmetics at its facility in Andheri East, Mumbai.

news.title: Telangana government land worth Rs 60,000 crore in ownership tussle
news.para: Located in high-demand and high-value areas such as Hafeezpet, Madhapur, and Kondapur, this land is at the centre of a legal battle with private firms and individuals claiming ownership.

news.title: Telangana launches LiDAR survey for 'One Map Hyderabad’ project
news.para: The ambitious light detection and ranging (LiDAR) survey will cover a range of crucial infrastructure details, including road network, water supply, electricity, sewage, and even fire and traffic police networks.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Pay property tax in advance, get up to 15% rebate in 2025-26
news.para: The decision was made while approving the civic body's Rs 15,502 crore budget for 2025-26. According to AMC, the advance payment rebate increased to 12% from the current 10%.

news.title: Asian Paints to exit Indonesia in nearly $6 million deal
news.para: Asian Paints said early last year that pursuing growth in Indonesia was "tough" due to profitability and cost control being under pressure.

news.title: Sebi proposes disclosure of financial information in offer documents for REITs, InvITs
news.para: These changes are based on the recommendations from the Working Group on Ease of Doing Business for REITs and InvITs, inputs from the Indian REITs Association and Bharat InvITs Association, and internal deliberations, Sebi said.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM calls for innovative urban development plans to meet sustainable housing needs
news.para: Tamil Nadu Chief Minister said efforts were on to prepare master plans for 136 cities, including Coimbatore, Madurai, Hosur, Salem, Tiruppur, Tiruchirappalli, Vellore and Tirunelveli.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body won’t acquire land from three villages for Harnandipuram
news.para: The township was proposed to come up on 521 hectares — almost the same size as Indirapuram — which would require the Authority to acquire land from 8 villages at an estimated Rs 5,000 crore.

news.title: GHMC to follow SC norms before razing illegal buildings in Hyderabad
news.para: GHMC commissioner K Ilambarithi recently issued detailed instructions with stage-wise actions to GHMC town planning officials and district collectors within GHMC limits.

news.title: Mumbai: 3,000 homebuyers stranded as HDIL projects stalled for years
news.para: A list of verified homebuyers shows they have collectively paid close to Rs 900 crore to the now-defunct HDIL but are still waiting for their apartments, many of which were booked about 15 years ago.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals over 20,000 properties with tax defaults
news.para: ​​The drive also resulted in a single-day tax collection of Rs 7.18 crore. The maximum number of properties sealed were in the East Zone, and the tax collected here was Rs 1.70 crore.

news.title: DDA plans survey to cover 173 more JJ clusters in Delhi
news.para: The database will be created in accordance with Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojna (Urban) requirements and used for determining the eligibility of slum dwellers for resettlement programmes.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC attaches DBS Realty’s 18 buildings in Chandivli over Rs 179 crore tax arrears
news.para: The BMC issues property attachment and seizure notices under Section 203 of the Mumbai Municipal Corporation Act to those who evade tax payment. And if the tax is not paid within the prescribed 21 days, auction of the property is initiated, said sources.

news.title: Six firms apply to straighten tilted buildings in Kolkata
news.para: The firms made the application after the civic body advertised seeking expression of interest from companies with expertise in such work to seek empanelment.

news.title: Odisha RERA imposes Rs 1 crore fine on realtor for violating registration norms
news.para: Hearing the case suo motu, a three-member bench of ORERA found that the realtor executing a mega project in Phulnakhara received the booking amount in 2018 when the Odisha Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016, was already in force.

news.title: Mumbai: Patra Chawl families reclaim homes after 15-year struggle
news.para: Patra Chawl in Siddharth Nagar, Goregaon West, a 47-acre Mhada layout, became embroiled in a land scam and political controversies. A redevelopment scheme resulted in Mhada land being sold to nine other developers.

news.title: Bigbloc Construction's net profit declines 96.64% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Bigbloc Construction's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 57.98 crore in Q3 FY25, a dip of 5.75 per cent from Rs 61.52 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
